HEADWORD: Emarginated
<hw>E*mar"gi*na`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the margin
interrupted by a notch or shallow sinus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Notched at the summit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Cryst.)</fld> <def>Having the edges
truncated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emarginately</ent>⟦br⟧
